<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🧊 M003 Extension 2 — English Worksheet (Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> 3D Mob Heads (x, y, z) · <strong>Course:</strong> 3D Coordinates · <strong>Level:</strong> Extension (Beginner, after Week 3) · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<p>Build a mob head in 3D. Now every block needs <strong>three</strong> numbers: <strong>(x, y, z)</strong>. x is <strong>across</strong>, y is <strong>up</strong>, z is <strong>forward</strong> (depth). The heads stand in front of you in the world — look at one as you build.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🔴 Stand on your <strong>home spot</strong> (red block) every run. Move, and the head moves too.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read the steps. Circle or write your answer.</p>
<pre><code>place green block at (3, 5, 1)
place green block at (3, 5, 2)
place green block at (3, 5, 3)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Only z changes. Circle one:</strong> across · up · deeper</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>place green block at (4, 5, 1)
place green block at (4, 6, 1)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Only y changes. Circle one:</strong> across · up · deeper</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Find the Difference 🐛</h2>
<p><strong>Correct</strong> first, then <strong>broken</strong>. Write one sentence about the bug.</p>
<p><strong>Pair A</strong> — This block should be one step deep: (3, 5, 2).</p>
<pre><code># correct
place green block at (3, 5, 2)
</code></pre>
<pre><code># broken
place green block at (3, 5, 1)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? Which number is different?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Pair B</strong> — The eye should be at (4, 7, 2).</p>
<pre><code># correct
place black block at (4, 7, 2)
</code></pre>
<pre><code># broken
place black block at (4, 2, 7)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? Which two numbers got swapped?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Fill the Gap ✏️</h2>
<p>To go <strong>deeper</strong>, the <strong>third</strong> number (z) grows. Fill the blanks to go deeper at (3, 5).</p>
<pre><code>place green block at (3, 5, 1)
place green block at (3, 5, __)
place green block at (3, 5, __)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Word bank:</strong> <code>2</code> · <code>3</code></p>
<p><strong>Write the two numbers:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Build a Head 🧱</h2>
<p>Look at the 🟢 creeper head in the world. Walk around it.</p>
<p><strong>Build the front face first</strong> (keep z = 1). Read each block's <strong>x</strong> (across) and <strong>y</strong> (up).</p>
<p><strong>Then add depth</strong> — build the same face again at z = 2, then z = 3.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>💡 Tip: the eyes and mouth only show on the <strong>front</strong>. The sides and back are plain.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Send a photo. Then finish these — 3 to 5 sentences.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I built the …</p>
<p>The lowest front block is at (x = …, y = …, z = …).</p>
<p>To go up I changed the … number; to go deeper I changed the … number.</p>
<p>My head is … blocks deep.</p>
<p>Next time I would …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + a photo on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
